BEIJING, Feb. 6 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake with a magnitude of 7.8 jolted 23 km E of Nurdağı, Turkey at 2023-02-06 01:17:36 GMT on Monday (2023-02-06 09:17:36 Beijing Time), the U.S. Geological Survey said. The epicenter, with a depth of 24.075 km, was initially determined to be at 37.2012 degrees north latitude and 36.9997 degrees east longitude. ■